With the increased demand for durable and cost-effective packaging solutions across various industries, the global cross-linked shrink film market is poised for significant growth by 2029. The market is segmented by type into polyethylene (PE), polypropylene (PP), and polyvinyl chloride (PVC). Among these, the polyethylene segment is expected to dominate the market owing to its versatility and widespread applications. Furthermore, based on thickness, the market is categorized into up to 50 microns, 50-100 microns, and above 100 microns, with the up to 50 microns segment likely to witness the highest growth rate. In terms of end-use industry, the food and beverages sector is anticipated to hold the largest market share, followed by pharmaceuticals, personal care and homecare, industrial, and others.

